{"type":"message","id":"635c4412","parentId":"2ff39dfc","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:21:51.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining Resource Allocation**\n\nI'm focused on optimizing token usage, particularly regarding the numerous Feishu tools. I've realized that submitting all thirty+ tools with every query is wasteful. The current approach is to identify which tools are essential for each turn and only submit those. This should dramatically reduce unnecessary token consumption.\n\n\n**Evaluating Tool Inclusion**\n\nI'm now prioritizing tool access. Removing `feishu_*` tools from `tools.alsoAllow` in `openclaw.json` seems like the cleanest approach. I'm exploring if removing them will allow use of the tools when they are needed. This could avoid a lot of schema overhead in API requests. My main goal here is to optimize token usage without limiting functionality.\n\n\n**Exploring Tool Loading Strategies**\n\nI'm now investigating dynamic tool loading to reduce token usage. I'm considering several approaches to avoid submitting all tools every time. Currently, I'm analyzing if `openclaw.json`'s `tools.alsoAllow` can be dynamically altered to enable tools on an as-needed basis. I'm exploring the nuances of `sessions_spawn` and subagents, along with custom skills within the `openclaw` context. The `tools.profiles` feature looks promising as well. My aim is flexible tool inclusion with efficient resource management.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b26acfb992720636","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/config.md | grep -A 20 \"tools\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":4392,"output":43,"cacheRead":36538,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40973,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568096116,"responseId":"