{"type":"message","id":"6d9c3c92","parentId":"44e0ff54","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:22:31.737Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining Feishu Logic**\n\nI'm currently working to refine the Feishu plugin's behavior. The goal is to avoid unnecessary activation and only enable the extra tools when genuinely required, or simply disable it from `plugins.allow` if the user just wants the core bot functionality without Feishu. The user wants to retain the bot's core capabilities while preventing the Feishu extension from being used every time.\n\n\n**Isolating Feishu Tools**\n\nI've made a crucial observation. By removing `tools.alsoAllow` from `openclaw.json`, the `openclaw-lark` tools will *only* activate when interacting on the Lark channel, instead of being unnecessarily injected into every single prompt. This should address the user's need to optimize token consumption and prevent the Feishu extension from being used every time. This feels like a significant breakthrough for the `feishu` plugin logic.\n\n\n**Exploring Subagent Alternatives**\n\nI'm now investigating subagents as a possible alternative. While `tools.alsoAllow` currently injects tools unconditionally, I'm exploring if a subagent could be spawned to specifically target the Lark tools. This aims to allow control over the Lark tools from the Web UI while keeping them separated from the standard prompt, which would meet the user's requirements. This method may offer greater control. However, I've noticed that `tools.alsoAllow` explicitly adds the tools to the agent. I'm looking under the `tools.profile`.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_caee9f4e0fc55dad","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get tools"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":3953,"output":18,"cacheRead":40572,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568140705,"responseId":"chatcmpl-55c0484f-4ec3-42b4-bc3d-da5842feb7c8"}}
