{"type":"message","id":"0aa159b0","parentId":"8bbdcf92","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:22:48.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Discovering Optimization Potential**\n\nI've made a breakthrough. I realized that by emptying `tools.alsoAllow` within `openclaw.json`, the Web UI will no longer inject the Feishu tools, which is a major token saver. The channel itself provides the tools when interacting with it, making this change safe.\n\n\n**Refining Tool Management Strategy**\n\nI've determined I can remove Feishu tools from `alsoAllow`. OpenClaw channel plugins automatically expose their tools, addressing concerns about Feishu channel usage. I also realize this affects the Web UI, which can still be handled. I am considering ways the user can toggle control over Feishu from the Web UI. I can tell the user about the changes, as well as a way to temporarily re-enable the tools.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9f20850280b0f797","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config set tools.alsoAllow '[]' --json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":25575,"output":26,"cacheRead":28442,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54043,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568159250,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b0aa0ac7-6385-40ae-ab7d-ef3a75f55cf8"}}
