{"type":"message","id":"a1024560","parentId":"6ecb8198","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:23:07.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining Token Management**\n\nI've made a breakthrough! By strategically emptying `tools.alsoAllow` within `openclaw.json`, the dreaded injection of Feishu tools via the Web UI will be avoided. This has the potential to dramatically reduce token consumption. The Feishu channel, fortunately, already provides the context necessary for its own tools.\n\n\n**Considering Dynamic Tool Loading**\n\nI'm now considering a dynamic tool loading approach. I need to make a strategic decision regarding user control over Feishu tools. While removing them from the global `alsoAllow` saves tokens by preventing unnecessary submission, I need to account for situations where the user wishes to control Feishu from the Web UI. A possible solution involves a subagent or temporary re-enabling of the tools as needed.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_254df57fbf9693d0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway restart"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":22800,"output":17,"cacheRead":28425,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568178114,"responseId":"chatcmpl-046b73de-1e66-4397-8a2e-2a5754239df2"}}
