{"type":"message","id":"2977e121","parentId":"fb7029fb","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:26:38.641Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Addressing the Optimization Issue**\n\nOkay, I'm delving into the optimizations performed and why the restart occurred. It seems the \"tools\" array is the crux, not just individual files, making broader optimization essential. I need to explain the restart more thoroughly and explore additional avenues for refinement.\n\n\n**Optimizing token consumption**\n\nI've discovered the root cause of the excessive token consumption! The 'tools.alsoAllow' configuration was bloated with numerous Feishu API tools, each with complex schemas, which were being injected globally. This was a critical configuration! I have addressed this by clearing this array. A configuration change needs to be applied, so a restart has been issued.\n\n\n**Verifying Configuration Settings**\n\nI need to confirm the configuration settings for the memory backend, specifically the `\"qmd\"` setting within `openclaw.json`. It seems I overlooked that the `memory.backend` was already set to `\"qmd\"`, meaning a configuration issue is unlikely to be the cause. I will now examine the openclaw configuration files more thoroughly, in an attempt to pinpoint the precise memory backend setting at the time of the token consumption issue.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1b6de3b31d340d8f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get memory"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":3168,"output":18,"cacheRead":32473,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35659,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568386947,"responseId":"chatcmpl-d218cc3e-fcc0-4de9-abd1-179f843913fa"}}
