{"type":"message","id":"ba96f85e","parentId":"3dcb2283","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:27:01.197Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_33a34ec6c0957225","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/docs.json:                      \"concepts/memory-qmd\",\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/images/feishu-step3-credentials.png matches\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/plugins/sdk-migration.md:  | `plugin-sdk/memory-core-host-engine-qmd` | Memory host QMD engine | Memory host QMD engine exports |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/plugins/sdk-overview.md:    | `plugin-sdk/memory-core-host-engine-qmd` | Memory host QMD engine exports |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:title: \"QMD Memory Engine\"\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:  - You want to set up QMD as your memory backend\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:# QMD Memory Engine\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:[QMD](https://github.com/tobi/qmd) is a local-first search sidecar that runs\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:- **Automatic fallback** -- if QMD is unavailable, OpenClaw falls back to the\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:- Install QMD: `npm install -g @tobilu/qmd` or `bun install -g @tobilu/qmd`\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:- QMD must be on the gateway's `PATH`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    backend: \"qmd\",\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:OpenClaw creates a self-contained QMD home under\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:`~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/qmd/` and manages the sidecar lifecycle\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:It prefers current QMD collection and MCP query shapes, but still falls back to\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:  configured `memory.qmd.paths`, then runs `qmd update` + `qmd embed` on boot\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:  `vsearch` and `query`). If a mode fails, OpenClaw retries with `qmd query`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:- If QMD fails entirely, OpenClaw falls back to the builtin SQLite engine.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:The first search may be slow -- QMD auto-downloads GGUF models (~2 GB) for\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:reranking and query expansion on the first `qmd query` run.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:QMD model environment variables pass through unchanged from the gateway\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:process, so you can tune QMD globally without adding new OpenClaw config:\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:export QMD_EMBED_MODEL=\"hf:Qwen/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-GGUF/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-Q8_0.gguf\"\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:export QMD_RERANK_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/reranker.gguf\"\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:export QMD_GENERATE_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/generator.gguf\"\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:Point QMD at additional directories to make them searchable:\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    backend: \"qmd\",\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:Snippets from extra paths appear as `qmd/<collection>/<relative-path>` in\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    backend: \"qmd\",\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:Transcripts are exported as sanitized User/Assistant turns into a dedicated QMD\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:collection under `~/.openclaw/agents/<id>/qmd/sessions/`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:By default, QMD search results are only surfaced in DM sessions (not groups or\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:channels). Configure `memory.qmd.scope` to change this:\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:    qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:Choose QMD when you need:\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:**QMD not found?** Ensure the binary is on the gateway's `PATH`. If OpenClaw\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:`sudo ln -s ~/.bun/bin/qmd /usr/local/bin/qmd`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:**First search very slow?** QMD downloads GGUF models on first use. Pre-warm\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:with `qmd query \"test\"` using the same XDG dirs OpenClaw uses.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:**Search times out?** Increase `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs` (default: 4000ms).\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:**Empty results in group chats?** Check `memory.qmd.scope` -- the default only\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:QMD traversal currently follows the underlying QMD scanner behavior rather than\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:hidden directories like `.tmp/` or outside indexed QMD roots until QMD exposes\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md:For the full config surface (`memory.qmd.*`), search modes, update intervals,\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:## Cross-agent QMD memory search\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:If one agent should search another agent's QMD session transcripts, add\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:extra collections under `agents.list[].memorySearch.qmd.extraCollections`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:Use `agents.defaults.memorySearch.qmd.extraCollections` only when every agent\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:        qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:          qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:    backend: \"qmd\",\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:    qmd: { includeDefaultMemory: false },\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory.md:<Card title=\"QMD\" icon=\"search\" href=\"/concepts/memory-qmd\">\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory.md:- [QMD Memory Engine](/concepts/memory-qmd) -- advanced local-first sidecar\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-builtin.md:Consider switching to [QMD](/concepts/memory-qmd) if you need reranking, query\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-honcho.md:|                   | Builtin / QMD                | Honcho                              |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-honcho.md:| **Dependencies**  | None (builtin) or QMD binary | Plugin install                      |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-honcho.md:Honcho and the builtin memory system can work together. When QMD is configured,\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/assets/openclaw-logo-text.png matches\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/assets/showcase/oura-health.png matches\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/assets/showcase/xuezh-pronunciation.jpeg matches\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/assets/showcase/bambu-cli.png matches\nBinary file /Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/assets/macos-onboarding/02-local-networks.jpeg matches\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:summary: \"All configuration knobs for memory search, embedding providers, QMD, hybrid search, and multimodal indexing\"\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:  - You want to set up the QMD backend\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:- [QMD Engine](/concepts/memory-qmd) -- local-first sidecar\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:the builtin engine ignores symlinks, while QMD follows the underlying QMD\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:`agents.list[].memorySearch.qmd.extraCollections` instead of `memory.qmd.paths`.\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:If the same resolved path appears in both `memory.qmd.paths` and\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:`memorySearch.qmd.extraCollections`, QMD keeps the first entry and skips the\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:## QMD backend config\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:Set `memory.backend = \"qmd\"` to enable. All QMD settings live under\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:`memory.qmd`:\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `command`                | `string`  | `qmd`    | QMD executable path                          |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:OpenClaw prefers the current QMD collection and MCP query shapes, but keeps\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:older QMD releases working by falling back to legacy `--mask` collection flags\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:QMD model overrides stay on the QMD side, not OpenClaw config. If you need to\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:override QMD's models globally, set environment variables such as\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:`QMD_EMBED_MODEL`, `QMD_RERANK_MODEL`, and `QMD_GENERATE_MODEL` in the gateway\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.commandTimeoutMs` | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD commands              |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.updateTimeoutMs`  | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD update operations     |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.embedTimeoutMs`   | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD embed operations      |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:Controls which sessio