y\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.commandTimeoutMs` | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD commands              |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.updateTimeoutMs`  | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD update operations     |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:| `update.embedTimeoutMs`   | `number`  | --      | Timeout for QMD embed operations      |\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:Controls which sessions can receive QMD search results. Same schema as\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:    qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:### Full QMD example\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:    backend: \"qmd\",\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/memory-config.md:    qmd: {\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md:- Memory search embedding provider readiness check (local model, remote API key, or QMD binary).\n/Users/hh/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md:- **QMD backend**: probes whether the `qmd` binary is available and startable.","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775568421189}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d195561","parentId":"ba96f85e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:27:09.189Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a958ffcb15bcd598","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":21564,"output":38,"cacheRead":12160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568421198,"responseId":"chatcmpl-065bbf41-530a-4a42-baeb-d09b3e261fb0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf650f4f","parentId":"9d195561","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:27:09.238Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a958ffcb15bcd598","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntitle: \"QMD Memory Engine\"\nsummary: \"Local-first search sidecar with BM25, vectors, reranking, and query expansion\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to set up QMD as your memory backend\n  - You want advanced memory features like reranking or extra indexed paths\n---\n\n# QMD Memory Engine\n\n[QMD](https://github.com/tobi/qmd) is a local-first search sidecar that runs\nalongside OpenClaw. It combines BM25, vector search, and reranking in a single\nbinary, and can index content beyond your workspace memory files.\n\n## What it adds over builtin\n\n- **Reranking and query expansion** for better recall.\n- **Index extra directories** -- project docs, team notes, anything on disk.\n- **Index session transcripts** -- recall earlier conversations.\n- **Fully local** -- runs via Bun + node-llama-cpp, auto-downloads GGUF models.\n- **Automatic fallback** -- if QMD is unavailable, OpenClaw falls back to the\n  builtin engine seamlessly.\n\n## Getting started\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Install QMD: `npm install -g @tobilu/qmd` or `bun install -g @tobilu/qmd`\n- SQLite build that allows extensions (`brew install sqlite` on macOS).\n- QMD must be on the gateway's `PATH`.\n- macOS and Linux work out of the box. Windows is best supported via WSL2.\n\n### Enable\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n  },\n}\n```\n\nOpenClaw creates a self-contained QMD home under\n`~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/qmd/` and manages the sidecar lifecycle\nautomatically -- collections, updates, and embedding runs are handled for you.\nIt prefers current QMD collection and MCP query shapes, but still falls back to\nlegacy `--mask` collection flags and older MCP tool names when needed.\n\n## How the sidecar works\n\n- OpenClaw creates collections from your workspace memory files and any\n  configured `memory.qmd.paths`, then runs `qmd update` + `qmd embed` on boot\n  and periodically (default every 5 minutes).\n- Boot refresh runs in the background so chat startup is not blocked.\n- Searches use the configured `searchMode` (default: `search`; also supports\n  `vsearch` and `query`). If a mode fails, OpenClaw retries with `qmd query`.\n- If QMD fails entirely, OpenClaw falls back to the builtin SQLite engine.\n\n<Info>\nThe first search may be slow -- QMD auto-downloads GGUF models (~2 GB) for\nreranking and query expansion on the first `qmd query` run.\n</Info>\n\n## Model overrides\n\nQMD model environment variables pass through unchanged from the gateway\nprocess, so you can tune QMD globally without adding new OpenClaw config:\n\n```bash\nexport QMD_EMBED_MODEL=\"hf:Qwen/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-GGUF/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-Q8_0.gguf\"\nexport QMD_RERANK_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/reranker.gguf\"\nexport QMD_GENERATE_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/generator.gguf\"\n```\n\nAfter changing the embedding model, rerun embeddings so the index matches the\nnew vector space.\n\n## Indexing extra paths\n\nPoint QMD at additional directories to make them searchable:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n    qmd: {\n      paths: [{ name: \"docs\", path: \"~/notes\", pattern: \"**/*.md\" }],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nSnippets from extra paths appear as `qmd/<collection>/<relative-path>` in\nsearch results. `memory_get` understands this prefix and reads from the correct\ncollection root.\n\n## Indexing session transcripts\n\nEnable session indexing to recall earlier conversations:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n    qmd: {\n      sessions: { enabled: true },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nTranscripts are exported as sanitized User/Assistant turns into a dedicated QMD\ncollection under `~/.openclaw/agents/<id>/qmd/sessions/`.\n\n## Search scope\n\nBy default, QMD search results are only surfaced in DM sessions (not groups or\nchannels). Configure `memory.qmd.scope` to change this:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    qmd: {\n      scope: {\n        default: \"deny\",\n        rules: [{ action: \"allow\", match: { chatType: \"direct\" } }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nWhen scope denies a search, OpenClaw logs a warning with the derived channel and\nchat type so empty results are easier to debug.\n\n## Citations\n\nWhen `memory.citations` is `auto` or `on`, search snippets include a\n`Source: <path#line>` footer. Set `memory.citations = \"off\"` to omit the footer\nwhile still passing the path to the agent internally.\n\n## When to use\n\nChoose QMD when you need:\n\n- Reranking for higher-quality results.\n- To search project docs or notes outside the workspace.\n- To recall past session conversations.\n- Fully local search with no API keys.\n\nFor simpler setups, the [builtin engine](/concepts/memory-builtin) works well\nwith no extra dependencies.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**QMD not found?** Ensure the binary is on the gateway's `PATH`. If OpenClaw\nruns as a service, create a symlink:\n`sudo ln -s ~/.bun/bin/qmd /usr/local/bin/qmd`.\n\n**First search very slow?** QMD downloads GGUF models on first use. Pre-warm\nwith `qmd query \"test\"` using the same XDG dirs OpenClaw uses.\n\n**Search times out?** Increase `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs` (default: 4000ms).\nSet to `120000` for slower hardware.\n\n**Empty results in group chats?** Check `memory.qmd.scope` -- the default only\nallows DM sessions.\n\n**Workspace-visible temp repos causing `ENAMETOOLONG` or broken indexing?**\nQMD traversal currently follows the underlying QMD scanner behavior rather than\nOpenClaw's builtin symlink rules. Keep temporary monorepo checkouts under\nhidden directories like `.tmp/` or outside indexed QMD roots until QMD exposes\ncycle-safe traversal or explicit exclusion controls.\n\n## Configuration\n\nFor the full config surface (`memory.qmd.*`), search modes, update intervals,\nscope rules, and all other knobs, see the\n[Memory configuration reference](/reference/memory-config)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":19,"aggregated":"---\ntitle: \"QMD Memory Engine\"\nsummary: \"Local-first search sidecar with BM25, vectors, reranking, and query expansion\"\nread_when:\n  - You want to set up QMD as your memory backend\n  - You want advanced memory features like reranking or extra indexed paths\n---\n\n# QMD Memory Engine\n\n[QMD](https://github.com/tobi/qmd) is a local-first search sidecar that runs\nalongside OpenClaw. It combines BM25, vector search, and reranking in a single\nbinary, and can index content beyond your workspace memory files.\n\n## What it adds over builtin\n\n- **Reranking and query expansion** for better recall.\n- **Index extra directories** -- project docs, team notes, anything on disk.\n- **Index session transcripts** -- recall earlier conversations.\n- **Fully local** -- runs via Bun + node-llama-cpp, auto-downloads GGUF models.\n- **Automatic fallback** -- if QMD is unavailable, OpenClaw falls back to the\n  builtin engine seamlessly.\n\n## Getting started\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Install QMD: `npm install -g @tobilu/qmd` or `bun install -g @tobilu/qmd`\n- SQLite build that allows extensions (`brew install sqlite` on macOS).\n- QMD must be on the gateway's `PATH`.\n- macOS and Linux work out of the box. Windows is best supported via WSL2.\n\n### Enable\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n  },\n}\n```\n\nOpenClaw creates a self-contained QMD home under\n`~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/qmd/` and manages the sidecar lifecycle\nautomatically -- collections, updates, and embedding runs are handled for you.\nIt prefers current QMD collection and MCP query shapes, but still falls back to\nlegacy `--mask` collection flags and older MCP tool names when needed.\n\n## How the sidecar works\n\n- OpenClaw creates collections from your workspace memory files and any\n  configured `memory.qmd.paths`, then runs `qmd update` + `qmd embed` on boot\n  and periodically (default every 5 minutes).\n- Boot refresh runs in the background so chat startup is not blocked.\n- Searches use the configured `searchMode` (default: `search`; also supports\n  `vsearch` and `query`). If a mode fails, OpenClaw retries with `qmd query`.\n- If QMD fails entirely, OpenClaw falls back to the builtin SQLite engine.\n\n<Info>\nThe first search may be slow -- QMD auto-downloads GGUF models (~2 GB) for\nreranking and query expansion on the first `qmd query` run.\n</Info>\n\n## Model overrides\n\nQMD model environment variables pass through unchanged from the gateway\nprocess, so you can tune QMD globally without adding new OpenClaw config:\n\n```bash\nexport QMD_EMBED_MODEL=\"hf:Qwen/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-GGUF/Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B-Q8_0.gguf\"\nexport QMD_RERANK_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/reranker.gguf\"\nexport QMD_GENERATE_MODEL=\"/absolute/path/to/generator.gguf\"\n```\n\nAfter changing the embedding model, rerun embeddings so the index matches the\nnew vector space.\n\n## Indexing extra paths\n\nPoint QMD at additional directories to make them searchable:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n    qmd: {\n      paths: [{ name: \"docs\", path: \"~/notes\", pattern: \"**/*.md\" }],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nSnippets from extra paths appear as `qmd/<collection>/<relative-path>` in\nsearch results. `memory_get` understands this prefix and reads from the correct\ncollection root.\n\n## Indexing session transcripts\n\nEnable session indexing to recall earlier conversations:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    backend: \"qmd\",\n    qmd: {\n      sessions: { enabled: true },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nTranscripts are exported as sanitized User/Assistant turns into a dedicated QMD\ncollection under `~/.openclaw/agents/<id>/qmd/sessions/`.\n\n## Search scope\n\nBy default, QMD search results are only surfaced in DM sessions (not groups or\nchannels). Configure `memory.qmd.scope` to change this:\n\n```json5\n{\n  memory: {\n    qmd: {\n      scope: {\n        default: \"deny\",\n        rules: [{ action: \"allow\", match: { chatType: \"direct\" } }],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nWhen scope denies a search, OpenClaw logs a warning with the derived channel and\nchat type so empty results are easier to debug.\n\n## Citations\n\nWhen `memory.citations` is `auto` or `on`, search snippets include a\n`Source: <path#line>` footer. Set `memory.citations = \"off\"` to omit the footer\nwhile still passing the path to the agent internally.\n\n## When to use\n\nChoose QMD when you need:\n\n- Reranking for higher-quality results.\n- To search project docs or notes outside the workspace.\n- To recall past session conversations.\n- Fully local search with no API keys.\n\nFor simpler setups, the [builtin engine](/concepts/memory-builtin) works well\nwith no extra dependencies.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**QMD not found?** Ensure the binary is on the gateway's `PATH`. If OpenClaw\nruns as a service, create a symlink:\n`sudo ln -s ~/.bun/bin/qmd /usr/local/bin/qmd`.\n\n**First search very slow?** QMD downloads GGUF models on first use. Pre-warm\nwith `qmd query \"test\"` using the same XDG dirs OpenClaw uses.\n\n**Search times out?** Increase `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs` (default: 4000ms).\nSet to `120000` for slower hardware.\n\n**Empty results in group chats?** Check `memory.qmd.scope` -- the default only\nallows DM sessions.\n\n**Workspace-visible temp repos causing `ENAMETOOLONG` or broken indexing?**\nQMD traversal currently follows the underlying QMD scanner behavior rather than\nOpenClaw's builtin symlink rules. Keep temporary monorepo checkouts under\nhidden directories like `.tmp/` or outside indexed QMD roots until QMD exposes\ncycle-safe traversal or explicit exclusion controls.\n\n## Configuration\n\nFor the full config surface (`memory.qmd.*`), search modes, update intervals,\nscope rules, and all other knobs, see the\n[Memory configuration reference](/reference/memory-config).","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775568429231}}
{"type":"message","id":"2626442c","parentId":"bf650f4f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:27:24.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Interpreting User Input**\n\nI'm currently working on understanding the user's questions, specifically focusing on the Chinese input. I'm breaking down \"你做了哪些优化？\" to determine the desired information regarding optimizations. Additionally, I'm analyzing the second query about restarts, aiming to identify the user's specific concern about disconnections and the underlying causes. I'm focusing on the request for a detailed explanation.\n\n\n**Analyzing Disconnection Reasons**\n\nI'm now investigating the brief disconnection and seeking a detailed explanation, which is crucial for my understanding. Additionally, I'm analyzing a user's third question about the tool list and a related question about potential optimizations, focusing on the configuration of qmd for memory management to reduce token consumption, specifically addressing their belief that the tool list might be the cause, and the previous configuration changes made to `openclaw.json`, specifically removing the large array of Feishu tools from `tools.alsoAllow` and restarting the process.\n\n\n**Confirming Configuration Impact**\n\nI've confirmed that restarting the OpenClaw gateway is essential after modifying `openclaw.json`, especially regarding tool permissions. This directly addresses the user's brief disconnection. The restart's impact is tied to the reduced token consumption; omitting those large Feishu tool schemas significantly cuts down on the payload size for each LLM request. The disconnection was precisely because the process shut down to start with the new configuration. This approach reduces token usage substantially.\n\n\n**Refining Optimization Strategies**\n\nI'm now focusing on optimizing the system further, specifically addressing memory management and token consumption as the user suggested. I will consolidate documentation files like `AGENTS.md`, `MEMORY.md`, and others. Only essential content for each turn will be kept, with detailed documentation moved to separate files that can be accessed via tools or memory search. I'll also refine skill descriptions, disable unused plugins, and explore using QMD for local-first search to reduce context bloat.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_56e8ee262cbd7ba5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which qmd"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":2915,"output":16,"cacheRead":32434,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35365,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568429239,"responseId":"chatcmpl-f465f5d1-83e3-458b-b79f-e6784c1b14ca"}}
