{"type":"message","id":"f5878d3e","parentId":"9c1f9beb","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:35:29.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Verifying the Log File**\n\nI'm now focused on verifying the log file, specifically checking `/Users/hh/Desktop/my/token.log` once more. I need to confirm if the optimizations have successfully removed the redundant tool definitions, particularly the Feishu extensions, and if the file size has decreased as a result.\n\n\n**Investigating the Increased File Size**\n\nI've been analyzing the findings from the `exec` call. The `ls -lh` output shows the log file `/Users/hh/Desktop/my/token.log` is now 157K, larger than before. This contradicts my expectations after optimization. The log indicates `model: gemini-3.1-pro-high` is now active, but redundant tool definitions persist, including schemas related to Feishu. The `openclaw.json` config should be disallowing it all. It seems the `openclaw-lark` plugin might be injecting the Feishu tools even though I've disabled them, or there is some logic conflict going on.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a1bc845636e1bee9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep '\"name\": \"feishu' /Users/hh/Desktop/my/token.log || echo \"No feishu tools\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":4460,"output":41,"cacheRead":61038,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65539,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775568919280,"responseId":"chatcmpl-37a6ae5b-7ade-4b82-98c1-e397e82cc29b"}}
